The paper proposes a new family of deep generative models for graphs, which involves the use of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) with attention. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as GNNs are a popular tool in this field. Additionally, the paper involves the use of mixture models, which are commonly used in probabilistic modeling and could suggest a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of node embeddings, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) for tasks such as image captioning. The paper's focus on efficiency and scalability could suggest a connection to Neural Networks (cs.NE) and Systems and Control (cs.SI).
